        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bingham, or near Dillon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon, Latta, Lake View, Sellers, Fork, Hamer, Oak Grove, South Of
The Border, Bingham, Floydale, Smithboro, Kemper, Little Rock, and
Mcleod Medical Center.

This includes Interstate 95 in South Carolina between mile markers
179 and 198.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
